  "title": "Preimage Distributes over Union and Intersection",
  "root": "",
  "statement": "Let $f:A\\to B$, $S,T\\subseteq B$. Then:\n- [label=(\\roman*)]\n- $f^{-1}(S\\cup T)=f^{-1}(S)\\cup f^{-1}(T)$.\n- $f^{-1}(S\\cap T)=f^{-1}(S)\\cap f^{-1}(T)$.\n- $f^{-1}(S^c)=(f^{-1}(S))^c$.",
